---
import ProjectCard from '../components/ProjectCard.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects">
	<h1 class="mb-4">Projects</h1>
	<p class="mb-4 text-caption italic">
		This is a subset of my best projects. I've made many minor contributions to various
		repositories and have others that are still in the works.
	</p>
	<h2 class="mb-2">My Projects</h2>
	<ul class="nolist mb-6 grid gap-1">
		<li>
			<ProjectCard
				name="This Website!"
				github="heftymouse/website"
				link="https://heftymouse.me"
				time="July 2023 - Present"
			>
				What you're reading right now! Inspired by
				<a href="https://www.figma.com/community/file/1159947337437047524/Windows-UI-3"
					>WinUI</a
				>, and built with Astro, Tailwind CSS and Cloudflare D1.
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
		<li>
			<ProjectCard name="Phobos" github="heftymouse/Phobos" time="July 2022 - Present">
				A browser for <a href="https://geminiprotocol.net">Geminispace</a>, a lightweight
				document protocol, made in WinUI 3 and C#.
				<a
					href="https://apps.microsoft.com/detail/Phobos/9N9MXC18ZX4L?launch=true&mode=mini"
				>
					<picture>
						<source
							srcset="https://get.microsoft.com/images/en-us%20light.svg"
							media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
						/>
						<img
							src="https://get.microsoft.com/images/en-us%20dark.svg"
							width="160"
							class="mt-2"
							alt="Get it from the Microsoft Store"
						/>
					</picture>
				</a>
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
		<li>
			<ProjectCard name="Arconia" github="heftymouse/arconia" time="July-September 2022">
				An incomplete WinUI 3 RCON client with a terrible name.
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
		<li>
			<ProjectCard name="BMTCMate" github="heftymouse/bmtcmate" time="July 2023">
				An iOS app I co-created for a hackathon. It adds a home screen widget showing you
				BMTC (Bengaluru's bus service) buses arriving at your nearest stop, and a function
				to track a route with a Live Activity.
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
		<li>
			<ProjectCard
				name="tsconverter"
				github="heftymouse/tsconverter"
				time="January 2023"
				link="https://heftymouse.github.io/tsconverter"
			>
				A super simple tool to turn <a href="https://terminal.sexy">terminal.sexy</a> links into
				Windows Terminal colour schemes.
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2 class="mb-2">Contributions</h2>
	<ul class="nolist grid gap-1">
		<li>
			<ProjectCard
				name="Files for Windows"
				github="files-community/Files"
				link="https://files.community"
			>
				I've helped add a handful of features to this app. Some of the highlights are swipe
				gestures for back/forward navigation, a GitHub action to automatically format Xaml
				files in pull requests, and support for changing system backdrop.
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
		<li>
			<ProjectCard
				name="discord-ban-appeals"
				github="Microsoft-community/discord-ban-appeals"
			>
				I added a system for tracking the state of appeals internally using Discord message
				components. I also ported the app from AWS Lambda to native Vercel functions.
			</ProjectCard>
		</li>
	</ul>
</BaseLayout>
